  > Rationale: 99 Speed Mart Sdn. Bhd. (operating under 99 Speed Mart Retail Holdings Bhd) is a highly established, dominant player in the Malaysian grocery retail sector. Founded in 2000, the company operates a massive, rapidly expanding network of proximity-based mini-markets (nearly 3,000 outlets). It commands approximately 40% of the Malaysian mini-market segment and over 10% of the broader grocery retail market. The company successfully completed Malaysia's largest IPO in seven years in September 2024, valuing the company at approximately RM16 billion. Its core business model relies on high-volume, low-margin sales of fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG), heavily supported by 'other operating income' such as display and distribution fees from suppliers. The operational profile is highly reputable, stable, and fully aligned with its claimed industry, presenting zero red flags or model discrepancies.
  - [INFO] 99 Speed Mart is the dominant market leader in Malaysia's mini-market sector, commanding approximately 40% market share in its segment and over 10% of the broader grocery retail market.
  - [INFO] The company operates a highly scalable, proximity-based retail model with nearly 3,000 outlets across Malaysia and a disciplined expansion strategy of adding approximately 250 new stores annually.
  - [INFO] Successfully completed Malaysia's largest Initial Public Offering (IPO) in seven years on September 9, 2024, raising RM2.36 billion and listing on the Main Market of Bursa Malaysia.
  - [INFO] The business model relies heavily on 'other operating income' (such as product display and distribution fees from suppliers) to generate net profits, as gross margins on direct FMCG sales are thin and primarily cover operational overheads.

